                             <div itemprop="articleBody">
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                               <span style="font-size:18px">
                                <strong>
                                 The Coastal House Plan: Casual and Informal Living on the Oceanfront
                                </strong>
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                Often thought of as a house on stilts (or piers) designed for relaxed and informal waterfront living, the coastal or beachfront house plan can be as trendy and chic as they come. From a simple vacation cottage to a modern and sophisticated home on the beach, coastal homes are perfect for those who love warm sea breezes wafting through the rooms, and the picturesque views of nature.
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                Coastal homes can be designed as one-story plans or multi-level structures with three or more bedrooms and all the amenities of waterfront living.
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                               <strong>
                                <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan130-1007Beachfront.JPG" style="height:284px; margin:7px; width:350px"/>
                                <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan16765.JPG" style="height:263px; width:350px"/>
                               </strong>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               Two house plans illustrate the pier and pile foundations. On the left is a four-bedroom design (two master suites), 3.5 baths, covered porch, and two-story open foyer.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16768">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16768
                               </a>
                               . The plan on the right has five bedrooms, two master suites, 4.5 baths, wraparound decks and covered entryway.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16765">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16765
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan9689.jpg" style="height:234px; margin:7px; width:350px"/>
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan9680FloorPlan_crop.jpg" style="height:300px; margin:7px; width:286px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               A one-story Florida-style home with three bedrooms and three baths. It has an open floor plan with easy access to kitchen/dining/living and outdoor space.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-9689">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-9680
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               <span style="font-size:16px">
                                <strong>
                                 <u>
                                  Features of a Coastal/Beachfront House Plan
                                 </u>
                                </strong>
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:.25in">
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                The most distinct feature of a coastal/beachfront house plan is
                                <strong>
                                 <em>
                                  an elevated main floor built on pier and pile foundations.
                                 </em>
                                </strong>
                                The stilt base protects the home from flooding and water damage to the interior. With the raised living area, parking is positioned below the home. While many coastal homes are built on piers or pilings, depending on your exact location and its flood risks, a home with an elevated crawl space or other foundation may be appropriate.
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:0.25in; text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan16759.JPG" style="height:344px; line-height:1.6em; margin:7px; width:517px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:1.0in">
                               <span style="font-size:12px">
                                A covered wraparound porch opens to the elevated living area of this coastal house plan. Parking is in the ground level of the home.
                               </span>
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16759" style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.6em;">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16759
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:1.0in">
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Covered entryways, stacked porches, decks and balconies provide great views, as do
                                </span>
                                <br/>
                               </li>
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Large windows  that also allow plenty of natural light into the home
                                </span>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p style="margin-left:1in; text-align:center">
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:1in; text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan16753.JPG" style="height:340px; margin:7px; width:453px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:1in; text-align:center">
                               This four-bedroom coastal house design has stacked porches, an open foyer and plenty of windows
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16753">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16753
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p style="margin-left:1.0in">
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Open floor plans that merge into one great room - living/dining/kitchen areas  making it easier for family and guests to socialize and interact with each other.
                                </span>
                                <br/>
                               </li>
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Materials such as stucco, concrete, and aluminum/vinyl/wood siding are used for exteriors; and asphalt shingle or metal for roofs
                                </span>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               <span style="font-size:16px">
                                <strong>
                                 <u>
                                  Casual and Comfortable Interiors
                                 </u>
                                </strong>
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                The focal point of a coastal/beachfront house plan is the waterfront view --- and interior designs and furnishings should highlight and enhance this aspect.
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 For starters, ensure that the view and natural landscapes are visible and clear at all times. Keep windows clean and instead of heavy curtains,
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   use decorative window shutters or blinds that filter the suns rays without obscuring the view.
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                </span>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/Plan22714.jpg" style="height:311px; line-height:1.6em; margin:7px; width:500px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               Check out the windows on this two-story, three-bedroom home that give a magnificent view of the surroundings. A glimpse into the interiors (photos below) shows an open floor plan with free-flowing traffic from the living-dining areas. Colorful cushions dress up the couch and chairs.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-22712">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-22714
                               </a>
                               .
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/22714Kitchen2.jpg" style="height:249px; margin:7px; width:400px"/>
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/22714LivingRoom2.jpg" style="height:249px; margin:7px; width:400px"/>
                               <br/>
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   Colors and tones associated with the ocean  blues, greens, shades of coral, beige
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 , interspersed with some soft browns, red and yellow hues  make the interior very appealing.
                                </span>
                                <br/>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/LivingRoom22712.jpg" style="height:300px; line-height:1.6em; width:401px"/>
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/16946Dining2.jpg" style="height:300px; margin:7px; width:400px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               A contrast of colors in these two great room areas achieves the same informal and casual effect. On the left, a splash of yellow, coral and beige
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16946">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-2
                               </a>
                               2712;and on the right, brown and white tones touched up with accessories (red flowers, plants) show a lived-in informal look.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-22712" style="line-height: 1.6em;">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-1
                               </a>
                               6946.
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Add some
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   nature accents in the interior dcor like plants, seashells, small rocks
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 from the beach seascape paintings on the walls or atop the fireplace mantel.
                                </span>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/LivingRoom2-16951.JPG" style="height:300px; width:400px"/>
                                <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/LivingRoom16951.JPG" style="height:350px; margin:7px; width:262px"/>
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               Touches of marine life in the dcor are visible in this coastal house plans interior. Shades that can be pulled up or down provide good views of the outdoors.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16951" style="line-height: 1.6em;">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16951
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 Choose
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   furniture that can survive beachfront living
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 -
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   comfortable sofas
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 with attractive and
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   washable slip covers
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                </span>
                                <br/>
                                <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                                 <li>
                                  <span style="font-size:14px">
                                   <strong>
                                    <em>
                                     Deck chairs and benches
                                    </em>
                                   </strong>
                                   made of rattan are perfect for the porches and balconies, and for optimum relaxation, have some throw pillows and cushions
                                  </span>
                                  <br/>
                                 </li>
                                 <li>
                                  <span style="font-size:14px">
                                   <strong>
                                    <em>
                                     Wood or tile floorings work best
                                    </em>
                                   </strong>
                                   and are easiest to maintain; have some soft and cushiony area rugs around the great room
                                  </span>
                                  <br/>
                                 </li>
                                </ul>
                               </li>
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 One or two
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   fireplaces
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 to keep everyone cozy and warm 
                                </span>
                                <br/>
                               </li>
                               <li>
                                <span style="font-size:14px">
                                 <strong>
                                  <em>
                                   Ceiling fans
                                  </em>
                                 </strong>
                                 are wonderful, especially in the summer months
                                </span>
                               </li>
                              </ul>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                              </p>
                              <p style="text-align:center">
                               <img alt="" src="http://www.theplancollection.com/admin/CKeditorUploads/Images/16951LivingArea.JPG" style="height:338px; margin:7px; width:450px"/>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               An area rug adorns the wood floor in the dining space. A ceiling fan is visible in the sitting area. And take a look at the abundance of windows in the room.
                               <a href="http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16951">
                                http://www.theplancollection.com/house-plans/home-plan-16951
                               </a>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                               <span style="font-size:14px">
                                So, are you ready for sun-filled days, the sound of waves, and gentle sea breezes? Perhaps its time for you to have that perfect beachfront dream home!
                               </span>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                              </p>
                             </div>
